        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/14837",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jeffrey",
                        "name": "jeffrey",
                        "displayName": "Jeffrey Sambells",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "From my testing this seems to be an issue with PDO and the way the execute wrapper is defined:\n\n<?\n    \/**\n     * Executes a prepared statement.\n     *\n     * @param array $params OPTIONAL Values to bind to parameter placeholders.\n     * @return bool\n     * @throws Zend_Db_Statement_Exception\n     *\/\n    public function execute(array $params = array())\n    {\n        try {\n            return $this->_stmt->execute($params);\n        } catch (PDOException $e) {\n            require_once 'Zend\/Db\/Statement\/Exception.php';\n            throw new Zend_Db_Statement_Exception($e->getMessage());\n        }\n    }\n?>\n\nif you execute the object without any parameters to the Zend execute method:\n\n$stmt->execute()\n\n$params is assigned an empty array. PDO them seems to use this empty array rather than the parameters from bindParam etc. if you change the function declaration to:\n\npublic function execute(array $params = null)\n\neverything begins to work again as without an input it now passes NULL to the PDO execute method rather than an empty array.\n\n  ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jeffrey",
                        "name": "jeffrey",
                        "displayName": "Jeffrey Sambells",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-05-29T12:10:04.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-05-29T12:10:04.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/14838",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jeffrey",
                        "name": "jeffrey",
                        "displayName": "Jeffrey Sambells",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Also, the default NULL values for $type in bindValue() (and possibly others) is also causing issues:\n\npublic function bindValue($parameter, $value, $type = null)\n\nIf you bind a value without specifying the $type with a PDO::PARAM_* value then the value becomes null when executed.\n\nI suggest changing it to:\n\n  public function bindValue($parameter, $value, $type = null)\n  {\n      if (is_string($parameter) && $parameter[0] != ':') {\n          $parameter = \":$parameter\";\n      }\n      try {\n          if(is_null($type)) { return $this->_stmt->bindValue($parameter, $value); }\n          return $this->_stmt->bindValue($parameter, $value, $type);\n      } catch (PDOException $e) {\n          require_once 'Zend\/Db\/Statement\/Exception.php';\n          throw new Zend_Db_Statement_Exception($e->getMessage());\n      }\n  }",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jeffrey",
                        "name": "jeffrey",
                        "displayName": "Jeffrey Sambells",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-05-29T12:25:19.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-05-29T12:25:19.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/14839",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Thanks for the help debugging, Jeffrey!  That did it -- at least for PDO adapters.\n\nThe fixes you suggest have been committed in revision 5048.  \n\nI'm going to leave this issue open for now, because I'd like to get it working across all adapters.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-05-29T13:36:35.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-05-29T13:36:35.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/15032",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This fix was included in 1.0.0 RC2, at least for PDO adapters.\n\nI have opened ZF-1475, ZF-1476, ZF-1477 for these binding features in IBM DB2, Oracle, and Mysqli.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
